<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Geocoding is the process of converting addresses (like "1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA") into geographic coordinates (like latitude 37.423021 and longitude -122.083739), which you can use to place markers on a map, or position the map.
</code></pre></div></div>
